# Git & Documentation Workflow

Courtify uses GitHub as the source of truth: https://github.com/andreduong/courtify

## When to commit and push

After completing a meaningful unit of work (feature, fix, config change, or docs update), **commit and push to origin** so progress is documented in the repo.

Do this at the end of a session when changes are stable, not after every single edit.

## Commit rules

- Write clear commit messages (1–2 sentences, focus on *why*)
- Stage only relevant files — never secrets or local artifacts
- **Never commit**: `.env`, `.dev.vars`, API keys, `RAPID_API_KEY`, Cloudflare tokens, or credentials
- Follow existing `.gitignore`; do not force-add ignored files

## Push rules

- Push to `origin` on the current branch after committing
- If the branch has no upstream: `git push -u origin HEAD`
- Do not force-push to `main` unless the user explicitly asks

## Documentation

- Update `AGENTS.md` when architecture, APIs, deployment steps, or agent workflows change
- Keep Worker JSON schema docs in sync with `index.js` when the payload shape changes

## Example end-of-task flow

```bash
git status
git add <relevant files>
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Add widget timeline provider wired to Worker API.

EOF
)"
git push -u origin HEAD
```
